The paper discusses a technique for debugging programs, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The implementation of the technique involves recording every state change in the program, which could be considered a programming languages (cs.PL) topic. The paper also presents a GUI for navigating through the program state, which could be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The integration with an event analyzer suggests a systems (cs.SY) aspect to the work. Finally, the paper discusses performance issues and possible optimizations, which could be considered a machine learning (cs.LG) topic.
